Usage: decompress_special [-help] [-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}] [-layers <layer>+]
                          [-nets <net>+]

-help                   # Prints out the command usage
-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}     # Specifies the coordinates for the area from which to
                        # decompress PG.
                        # Only special wires and special vias within the
                        # specified area will be decompressed.
                        # Default: Decompress all PG structure. (box, optional)
-layers <layer>+        # Specifies the layers on which to decompress PG. You
                        # must use LEF layer names or a routing layer index
                        # value (1 for the first routing layer, 2 for the
                        # second routing layer, and so on). ((layer)+, optional)
-nets <net>+            # Specifies the nets from which to decompress PG.
                        # ((net)+, optional)